  "texts": [
    "The main advantage of MBDTA is that it uses real execution data, which inherently includes the actual behavior of the hardware and software under test, providing a high degree of practical relevance.Hansen et al. [70] discuss statistical-based WCET estimation and validation.",
    "Their work explores the use of statistical methods to analyze the variability in execution times and proposes techniques to estimate the WCET more accurately.",
    "This approach provides a framework for incorporating statistical analysis into MBDTA, improving the precision of WCET estimates by considering the probabilistic distribution of execution times.Lundqvist et al. [71] explore practical WCET analysis approaches based on testing.",
    "They emphasize the importance of using extensive testing to gather execution time data and discussed methods to derive WCET estimates from this data.",
    "Their work highlights the challenges of ensuring that test inputs cover the worst-case scenarios and proposed strategies to enhance test coverage and accuracy."
  ],
